    "long_instructions": "An online marketplace needs to filter search results by removing irrelevant products based on user search queries.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Marketplace</code> class, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">filterSearchResults()</code> method to remove all non-relevant products from the list of products.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">MarketplaceRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">filterSearchResults()</code> method and print the result.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the documentation for the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">ArrayList</code> class in the <strong>Documentation</strong> tab ⬆️ for help with using the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">remove()</code> method.\r\n</div>",
